## Map Over Lookups

Sketch that looks up a list of topics, retrieves each, and formats them:

```scheme
;; SKETCH (three steps)
(define topics '(\"breakfast\" \"weather\" \"calendar\"))
(define facts (map (lambda (t) (cortex/recall :topic t)) topics))
(map (lambda (f) (string-append \"• \" (or f \"—\"))) facts)
```

Collapse:

```scheme
;; ONE SHOT
(map (lambda (t) 
       (string-append \"• \" 
                      (or (cortex/recall :topic t) \"—\"))) 
     '(\"breakfast\" \"weather\" \"calendar\"))
```

*[needs: cortex/recall]*

The recall happens *inside* the map. One form. No `facts`. The data flows from the list, through the lambda, into the append, and the paren closes.

