## Fold With Guard

Sketch that folds a list of numbers, but only if they're positive:

```scheme
;; SKETCH (three steps)
(define nums '(3 -2 7 0 5))
(define positive (filter (lambda (n) (> n 0)) nums))
(fold + 0 positive)
```

Collapse:

```scheme
;; ONE SHOT
(fold + 0 
      (filter (lambda (n) (> n 0)) 
              '(3 -2 7 0 5)))
```

The filter closes inside the fold. If the list came from a recall:

```scheme
;; ONE SHOT (recall in place)
(fold + 0 
      (filter (lambda (n) (> n 0)) 
              (or (cortex/recall :topic \"daily-steps\") '())))
```

*[needs: cortex/recall]*

The recall is guarded with `or`, filtered, and folded—all in one form.

