## Speech With Inline Recall

Sketch that recalls a name, formats a greeting, and speaks it:

```scheme
;; SKETCH (three steps)
(define name (cortex/recall :topic \"user.name\"))
(define greeting (string-append \"Good morning, \" (or name \"friend\") \"!\"))
(surface :say greeting)
```

Collapse:

```scheme
;; ONE SHOT
(surface :say (string-append \"Good morning, \" 
                             (or (cortex/recall :topic \"user.name\") \"friend\") 
                             \"!\"))
```

*[needs: cortex/recall, surface :say]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire cortex + speech surface -->

The recall is guarded, appended, and spoken—all in one form. The data flows inward, and the paren closes at the speech boundary.

