## Honest Null With Escalation

Sketch that tries to recall a fact, and escalates if it's missing:

```scheme
;; SKETCH (two steps)
(define fact (cortex/recall :topic \"medication-time\"))
(if fact fact (escalate :reason \"No medication schedule stored.\"))
```

Collapse:

```scheme
;; ONE SHOT
(or (cortex/recall :topic \"medication-time\") 
    (escalate :reason \"No medication schedule stored.\"))
```

*[needs: cortex/recall, escalate]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire cortex + escalate surface -->

The `or` short-circuits. If the recall succeeds, the escalate never runs. If the recall returns `#f`, the escalate fires and the form ends. One honest-null shot.

