## Conditional Wire Fetch

Sketch that checks the time, and fetches data only during business hours:

```scheme
;; SKETCH (four steps)
(define now (clock/now))
(define hour (string->number (substring now 11 13)))
(define should-fetch (and (>= hour 9) (< hour 17)))
(if should-fetch (fetch \"https://api.example.com/office-status\") 'closed)
```

Collapse:

```scheme
;; ONE SHOT
(if (let ((hour (string->number (substring (clock/now) 11 13)))) 
      (and (>= hour 9) (< hour 17))) 
    (fetch \"https://api.example.com/office-status\") 
    'closed)
```

*[needs: clock/now, fetch]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire clock + fetch -->

The `let` extracts the hour from `clock/now`. The `and` checks the range. The `if` decides whether to fetch. One form. No `now`. No `hour`. No `should-fetch`.

