## Recall + Transform + Store

Sketch that recalls a list, transforms it, and stores it back:

```scheme
;; SKETCH (three steps)
(define old-list (cortex/recall :topic \"shopping-list\"))
(define new-list (cons \"milk\" (or old-list '())))
(store :shopping-list new-list)
```

Collapse:

```scheme
;; ONE SHOT
(store :shopping-list 
       (cons \"milk\" 
             (or (cortex/recall :topic \"shopping-list\") '())))
```

*[needs: cortex/recall, store]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire cortex + store -->

The recall is guarded, consed, and stored—all in one form. The data flows from recall to cons to store, and the paren closes at the storage boundary.

