## Nested Let for Readability

Sketch that computes intermediate values for clarity:

```scheme
;; SKETCH (four steps)
(define width 10)
(define height 5)
(define area (* width height))
(string-append \"Area: \" (number->string area) \" sq m\")
```

Collapse with nested `let`:

```scheme
;; ONE SHOT
(let ((width 10) 
      (height 5)) 
  (let ((area (* width height))) 
    (string-append \"Area: \" (number->string area) \" sq m\")))
```

Or flatten the `let*`:

```scheme
;; ONE SHOT (let*)
(let* ((width 10) 
       (height 5) 
       (area (* width height))) 
  (string-append \"Area: \" (number->string area) \" sq m\"))
```

Both are one form. The bindings live only for the body. No top-level `define`.

