## Wire Fetch + Parse + Guard

Sketch that fetches JSON, parses it, and guards against missing fields:

```scheme
;; SKETCH (four steps)
(define response (fetch \"https://api.example.com/data.json\"))
(define parsed (json/parse response))
(define temp (assoc 'temperature parsed))
(if temp (cdr temp) 'nan)
```

Collapse:

```scheme
;; ONE SHOT
(let ((parsed (json/parse (fetch \"https://api.example.com/data.json\")))) 
  (if (assoc 'temperature parsed) 
      (cdr (assoc 'temperature parsed)) 
      'nan))
```

*[needs: fetch, json/parse]*  
<!-- BUILD: wire fetch + JSON parsing -->

The fetch closes inside the parse, the parse closes inside the `let`, the `assoc` is checked and dereferenced in the `if`. One form. The guard is honest: if the field is missing, return `'nan`.

