## Fold With Nested Lookup

Sketch that folds a list, looking up a multiplier for each element:

```scheme
;; SKETCH (two steps)
(define items '(\"apples\" \"oranges\" \"bananas\"))
(fold (lambda (item acc) 
        (+ acc (* (cortex/recall :topic (string-append \"price.\" item)) 1))) 
      0 
      items)
```

Collapse:

```scheme
;; ONE SHOT
(fold (lambda (item acc) 
        (+ acc (or (cortex/recall :topic (string-append \"price.\" item)) 0))) 
      0 
      '(\"apples\" \"oranges\" \"bananas\"))
```

*[needs: cortex/recall]*

The recall happens *inside* the fold's lambda. The fallback is guarded with `or`. One form. No `items`.

