## Map Over Nested Lookups

Sketch that maps a list, looking up metadata for each element and transforming it:

```scheme
;; SKETCH (two steps)
(define items '(\"apple\" \"banana\" \"cherry\"))
(map (lambda (item) 
       (string-append item \": \" 
                      (number->string 
                        (or (cortex/recall :topic (string-append \"price.\" item)) 0)))) 
     items)
```

Collapse:

```scheme
;; ONE SHOT
(map (lambda (item) 
       (string-append item \": \" 
                      (number->string 
                        (or (cortex/recall :topic (string-append \"price.\" item)) 0)))) 
     '(\"apple\" \"banana\" \"cherry\"))
```

*[needs: cortex/recall]*

The recall happens *inside* the map's lambda. One form. No `items`.

