## Fold With Conditional Accumulation

Sketch that folds a list, accumulating only values that meet a condition:

```scheme
;; SKETCH (two steps)
(define nums '(3 7 2 9 4))
(fold (lambda (n acc) 
        (if (> n 5) (+ acc n) acc)) 
      0 
      nums)
```

Collapse:

```scheme
;; ONE SHOT
(fold (lambda (n acc) 
        (if (> n 5) (+ acc n) acc)) 
      0 
      '(3 7 2 9 4))
```

The conditional is *inside* the fold's lambda. One form. No `nums`.

