## Wire Fetch + Map + Fold

Sketch that fetches a list, maps it, and folds it:

```scheme
;; SKETCH (four steps)
(define response (fetch \"https://api.example.com/items\"))
(define items (cdr (assoc 'items response)))
(define values (map (lambda (i) (cdr (assoc 'value i))) items))
(fold + 0 values)
```

Collapse:

```scheme
;; ONE SHOT
(fold + 0 
      (map (lambda (i) (cdr (assoc 'value i))) 
           (cdr (assoc 'items (fetch \"https://api.example.com/items\")))))
```

*[needs: fetch]*

The fetch closes inside the `assoc`, the `assoc` closes inside the map, the map closes inside the fold. One form. No `response`. No `items`. No `values`.

