## Knowledge + Recall + Transform + Speech

Sketch that looks up knowledge, recalls a preference, transforms both, and speaks the result:

```scheme
;; SKETCH (five steps)
(define fact (knowledge/of :category \"birds\"))
(define name (cdr (assoc 'name (car fact))))
(define pref (cortex/recall :topic \"favorite.bird\"))
(define message (string-append \"The \" name \" is a bird. Your favorite: \" (or pref \"unknown\") \".\"))
(surface :say message)
```

Collapse:

```scheme
;; ONE SHOT
(surface :say 
         (string-append \"The \" 
                        (cdr (assoc 'name (car (knowledge/of :category \"birds\")))) 
                        \" is a bird. Your favorite: \" 
                        (or (cortex/recall :topic \"favorite.bird\") \"unknown\") 
                        \".\"))
```

*[needs: knowledge/of, cortex/recall, surface :say]*

The knowledge lookup, the recall, the transformations, and the speech all happen in one form. No `fact`. No `name`. No `pref`. No `message`.

